I'm twenty nine, no kids, never married I like to play sports, listen to music, read etc. . . Despite how I write I'm a really silly guy and don't try to take too many things too seriously because of this, plus life's short. I live in California, but that doesn't mean the woman for me has to be here as well. I don't think the woman for me has to be within a thirty-mile radius and it's pretty narrow-minded to think so. I'm looking for a woman who is willing to visit California, I understand not everyone would be and that's find just disregard this whole ad if this isn't you. If it is then keep reading. As far as the kind of women I like I like sweet women who have an innocent side but also a freaky one when need be, someone clean of course, faithful, loyal and not a liar. I'm not into married women or women who are still living with their ex or who sleep around a lot. Physically I like a big thick woman who has very large/'huge breast over D D D a lot of women think they do, (or try to give the illusion they do by standing sideways), but I've noticed they don't, at least not to my standard. I'm half black and Italian;

I tend not to care about race too much though. Also I can't cook so if I do find a special girl who wants to visit, if you can't cook then T.V dinners is what's on the menu, yummy.

Well if interested, please message me and send a full picture, I won't respond without one simply because I'll assume its spam and PLEASE PLEASE no gay guys. I'm not gay, I'm not bi, never have been never will be, please get it through your head, I only like women, it's a shame all these beautiful women are running out of a selection of straight guys these days.

I've been thinking about just what it is that would suit me regarding a relationship with a woman. I've been married, now divorced for several years, and I really don't feel like I want, or need to be married again. Still, I am a one woman man, I am not a serial dater. I have never been interested in dating several women, and I most definitely do not want just a sex partner. Man or woman, anyone who easily has sex just for the sake of sex, is a tramp.

So I'm thinking something in between. Call it... Friends and lovers. I suppose some might call this "Friends with benefits," but somehow, that sounds a little crass, a little too distant. 

Following are ten good reasons why I will be an excellent Friend and Lover.

I will treat you with courtesy and respect. Not because I am playing you, but because I really do respect you.

Our friendship will be real, and we will do friendly things together. Dinner dates, movies, concerts, plays, or just going out for ice cream (in the summer), or a hot cup of tea (in the winter). I have a great sense of humor and we will frequently share a good laugh.

When I ask about your day, it will be because I really am interested, and I want to be there for you when you need someone to listen.

I am real. I am genuine. I have ruggedly chiseled features, and I am in excellent, athletic physical condition. I am also very normal, I'm not one of those Craigslist trollers who thinks the way to attract a woman is to post a photo of erect genitalia.

I am intelligent, educated, and engaged in the larger world around me. I know the proper uses for to, too, and two, as well as there, their, and they're.

I am well groomed. I take pride in my appearance. I always practice good hygiene, and I have never used alcohol, tobacco, or illicit drugs.

I will not call, text, or email you only when I'm in the mood for sex. I may just ask if you want to catch a movie, grab a bite to eat, or spend some time chatting over a cup of coffee.

I realize that the "Lovers" aspect of friends and lovers necessarily requires a mutual attraction. There must be chemistry, a reciprocal spark. There is an axiom that states: "When a woman meets a man for the first time, she will know within no more than one or two minutes, if she will ever be intimate with him." I am perfectly willing to meet with you, and accept whatever happens, or does not happen.

I can be an exciting and adventurous lover. I am open to exploring new things when intimate encounters occur. I will hug you and show you heartfelt tenderness, if that is what you need, or I'll thrown you down on your bed and tear your cloths off, if that is what you want.

I believe that there is a real possibility for that "in between" relationship of friends and lovers. And if, over time, something more should develop, I'm open to such a possibility.


So, if I've piqued your interest, there is still the matter of compatibility. There is little point to pursuing a friends and lovers relationship if we do not share similar interests and values. Following is a list that will give you a pretty good idea of my personality.


If you would wear a T-shirt that bears the phrase, "You say socialism as if it were a bad thing,"
if you surmise that Sarah Palin is as imbecilic and as dangerous as a nuclear hand grenade,
if you realize the one intelligent statement George W. Bush ever made is "Tacos rule,"
if you understand that the Earth is 4.5 billion years old, NOT 6,000 years old,
If you think that Bill Nye and Neil deGrasse Tyson should be the Secretaries of Explaining the Real World to Conservatives,
if you are sure that 665 is the birthmark on Rush Limbaugh's head,
if you believe that Baruch Spinoza was 400 years ahead of his time,
if you subscribe to Carl Jung's thesis of the Collective Unconscious,
if you grasp John Donne's conviction that "No man (or woman) is an island,"
if you are averse to being lonely, but you value occasional solitude,
if your circle of friends is smaller, intimate and real, rather than a large group of acquaintances,
if you enjoy ballroom dancing, Tango, Cha Cha, Swing,
if you would rather watch Antiques Road Show than televised sports,
if you would sooner spend an evening at an art gallery or a museum than a bar,
if you enjoy Art a Whirl and other art crawls,
if your car radio is usually tuned to NPR / MPR,
if you understand that Arts Education is just as important as "Readin' Ritin' and 'Rithmatic,"
if you much prefer a quiet booth in an elegant restaurant to a noisy night club,
if you find "The Venture Brothers" smartly written and hysterically funny,
if you know that being sarcastic is a negative, mean spirited attribute, while a satirical wry wit is a positive attribute,
if your inner geek gets excited when the new Macs come out,
if you love expressing your artistic vision through photography and Photoshop,
if your favorite movies include Casablanca, Love and Death, Man of La Mancha, The Bourne Trilogy, The English Patient, Defending Your Life,
if your iPod playlist includes Mozart, Glenn Miller, Vic Damone, Patsy Cline, Elvis, Donna Summer, The Moody Blues, Rhythm & Blues,
if you could drink maple syrup (REAL maple syrup) right from the jar, but you control yourself,
if you are a chocoholic but you have it under control (no, really, I do have it under control),
if your perfect pizza is thin crust, overflowing sauce, blanketed in pepperoni & sausage, but absitively, posolutely NO cheese,
if you eschew tobacco, drugs (yes, marijuana is a drug), and alcohol (beyond social drinking),
if you know what P90X is,
if you have an older soul but are young at heart,
if you think kissing your cat (or dog) on the top of its fuzzy head is a good thing,
if you love what a pair of 5 inch stiletto heels does for your legs,
if you spurn pantyhose in favor of back seam thigh high stockings, 
if you swoon when slipping into silky lingerie your man picked out for you,
if intellectual curiosity is an attribute you seek in a partner,
if you know what makes you So Very SEXY is your Big, Big... Brain,
if you appreciate a chivalrous man who opens doors for you,
if you experience ardor and safety when enveloped in your man's protecting arms,
if you are warmed by the sensation of your man's hand in the small of your back,
if the sound of your man's voice brings a smile to your lips,
if the sight of your approaching man puts that sparkle in your eyes...

perhaps we should talk.

Well, if you are now smiling and laughing, rather than running, screaming, away from your computer,
perhaps we share a similar sense of wit and humor.

Should providence favor me, I'll hear back from you before long.

