Hi!
I am white, 6'3, in my mid-30s, full hair, tan and successful. I am looking for someone to have a good time with! A perfect match would be a cute girl that likes to be spoiled and given a lot of attention. Is that you? I would love to find the right girl that eventually wants to be a travel companion with me and get out of MN in the winters! Please send a picture and a little about you. I have more to share about me after I know you are real. Looking forward to talking with you soon. Have a great day!! ;)

First off, I'm 48, male, I could certainly afford to lose a few pounds but I blame my age and am working on that every day. I do not smoke. I am anxiously waiting for the weather to turn nice once again so that I can get back to walking and biking. I work quite a few hours during the week but my weekends are totally free. I have a nice home. I have a boat I love to be on in the summer. Sounds pretty good, right? Wrong. So wrong. I've got a huge problem. You see, I've got this empty home now and in the summer I will have my boat and, well, there's no one else in either one of them. Big problem. Not okay. What I need is a co-captain and best friend. 
Co-captain and best friend requirements include: 
1.	must be between 43-50; 
2.	not required to laugh at bad jokes, but must have a high tolerance for them; 
3.	must love bon fires and grilling, but I can cook and actually enjoy it; 
4.	a sharp wit is priority; 
5.	must possess hopelessly romantic tendencies; 
6.	must be patient with my busy weekday schedule; 
7.	must have brilliant, beautiful, strong mind of her own. 
8. non-smoker - light drinker
I love sports, being outdoors, playing golf, reading, and working on my yard and garden in the summer...not necessarily all together or in that particular order. I've heard my back rubs are as lousy as my memory, and my eyesight that seems to be going as well so maybe you can help at least improve on my back rubs and memory. I love a beautiful woman with a goofy laugh as much as I love a goofy-looking woman with a beautiful laughe. I am a terrible dancer and I cannot sing, but if you want I will go dancing and will sing in the car or shower if nobody is listening. 
I want my companion to be my best friend, my confidante, my rock, and, of course, someone to watch a hocky game with, work out with or help pull the anchor up on the boat and work in my garden in the summer. 
If we were all honest with ourselves we would admit that most of us have failed in a previous relationship. I would hope that you have learned from yours like I have learned from mine. Relationships need both parties to work at it. That requires compassion, communication, vulnerability, and honesty. If we work on these core values you can make any relationship work. I also believe that most good relationships start out as a strong friendship that eventually leads to more. Seems simple right? It does not seem to be.
I also understand that there should be an attraction, I'm not oblivious to that fact. If you do not think that I am attractive all I can say is good luck to you and say goodbye with a smile. I will not post a pic on this ad but if you send one or request one I will oblige. If I find you attractive I will send you an email to start some dialogue between the two of us. That first email is always the hardest.
Do you have the nevrve to take a chance?
